<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>System Administration</div><div><br /></div><div><br /></div><div><span style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: bold; line-height: normal;">How To Add a User to "sudo" group:</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">=&gt; sudo visudo</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">root ALL=(ALL)  ALL</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">%admin ALL=(ALL)  NOPASSWD: ALL</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">username ALL=(ALL) ALL</span></div><div><br /></div><div><span style="font-size: 19px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: bold; line-height: normal;">How to use the "dscl" command:</span></div><div><br /></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;"># Use the command "dscl" (Directory Service command line utility)</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;"># Create a new entery:</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;"># =&gt; sudo dscl [space] . [space] /Users/&lt;username&gt; </span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">=&gt; sudo dscl . create /Users/testuser</span></div><div><br /></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;"># Set the Login Shell</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">=&gt; sudo dscl . /Users/testuser UserShell /bin/bash</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;"> </span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;"># Set the USER's name:</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">=&gt; sudo dscl . /Users/testuser RealName "Test User"</span></div><div><br /></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;"># Set the USER's ID ( UID):</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">=&gt; sudo dscl . /Users/testuser UniqueID 501</span></div><div><br /></div><div><br /></div><div><br /></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;"># Set the USER's Primary GROUP ID ( UID):</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">=&gt; sudo dscl . /Users/testuser PrimaryGroupID 1001</span></div><div><br /></div><div><br /></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;"># To change a USER password:</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">=&gt; sudo dscl . passwd /Users/khasanov &lt;Hydrogen3&gt;</span></div><div><br /></div><div><br /></div><div><br /></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;"># Add the "khasanov" to the Group "www" ( or "_www")</span></div><div><span style="font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">=&gt; sudo dscl . append /Groups/</span><a href="http://www GroupMembership" style="font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">www GroupMembership</a><span style="font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;"> khasanov</span></div><div><br /></div><div><br /></div><div><br /></div><div><br /></div><div><span style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: bold; line-height: normal;">Restore Macbook Pro</span></div><div><br /></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">1.</span><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">Restart the Laptop while holding COMMAND and R keys until the Mac OS X Utilities window appeared</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">2.</span><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">Select Disk Utilities (DU) from the Mac OS X Utilities window and click on the Continue button.</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">3.</span><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">After DU loads select your startup volume (usually Macintosh HD) from the left side list.</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">4.</span><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">Click on the Erease tab in the DU main window.</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">5.</span><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">Set the format type to Mac OS Extended (Journaled). Click on the Security button and set the Zone Data option to one-pass.</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">6.</span><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">Click on the </span><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: bold; line-height: normal;">Erase</span><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;"> button and wait until the process has completed.</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">7.</span><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">Quit DU and return to the Mac OS X Utilities window.</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">8.</span><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">Select Reinstall Lion/Mountain Lion and click on the </span><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: bold; line-height: normal;">Install</span><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;"> button.</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">9.</span><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">Upon completion shutdown the computer.</span></div><div><br /></div><div><br /></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: bold; line-height: normal;">Note:</span><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;"> </span><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: italic; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">If your computer came with Lion or Mountain Lion pre-installed then you are entitled to transfer your license once.</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: italic; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;"> If you purchased Lion or Mountain Lion from the App Store then you cannot transfer your license to another party. In the </span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: italic; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">case of the latter you should install the original version of OS X that came with your computer. You need to repartition</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: italic; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;"> the hard drive as well as reformat it; this will assure that the Recovery HD partition is removed. See Step Three above. </span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: italic; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">You may verify these requirements by reviewing your OS X Software License.</span></div></en-note>